Here are the deficiencies of bitcoin. I know they will be rebutted till exhaustion but they&#x27;re deficiencies nonetheless.<p><pre><code>    - 20 million
    - eight decimals
    - blockchain size
    - cryptic account ids
    - QR codes
    - price instability
    - latency
    - privacy
    - reach
</code></pre>
The typical responses will be<p><pre><code>    &quot;that&#x27;s a feature not a bug&quot; 
    &quot;you&#x27;ll get used to decimals&quot; 
    &quot;qr codes are not that hard&quot; 
    &quot;in a decade everybody will have a petabyte in their phones&quot;
    &quot;ten minutes is not that long&quot;
    &quot;who needs privacy if they&#x27;re not doing anything wrong&quot;
    &quot;to the moon!&quot;
</code></pre>
And that&#x27;s the precise state in which a disrupting technology hits you with your pants down.<p>Blindness.
